{"source_key":"sha256-31ae2543195c19275814384bf971ff26","record_index":1877,"record_hash":"sha256:070a95b12fdba731e830d87c7ef9fbcd812d85fe513e751d27d577d7cae98a5c","timestamp":"2026-05-25T08:56:05.993Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: 8e1f77\nWall time: 0.3510 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 990\nOutput:\n{\"data\":{\"repository\":{\"pullRequest\":{\"reviewThreads\":{\"nodes\":[{\"id\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"isResolved\":true,\"isOutdated\":true,\"path\":\"crates/but-agentlog/src/redaction.rs\",\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"copilot-pull-request-reviewer\"},\"body\":\"`redact_string` only considers path redaction after the `MIN_CANDIDATE_LEN` check. That means absolute paths shorter than 20 characters (e.g. `/tmp/a`, `/a/b`) will never be replaced with `[REDACTED:path]`, which can still leak local filesystem details. Consider checking for absolute-path patterns before the length threshold (or using a separate, smaller threshold for paths) so short absolute paths are consistently redacted. Also note that Windows absolute paths (e.g. `C:\\\\Users\\\\...`) aren't detected by `is_absolute_path_candidate` / the token scan and will currently pass through in plain text.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/gitbutlerapp/gitbutler/pull/13938#discussion_r3297041282\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-25T08:41:59Z\"}]}},{\"id\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"isResolved\":true,\"isOutdated\":true,\"path\":\"crates/but-agentlog/src/transcript.rs\",\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"copilot-pull-request-reviewer\"},\"body\":\"`prompt_source` currently allocates a new `String` just to do a lookup/removal in `spawn_prompts` (`spawn_prompts.remove(normalized_prompt(text).as_str())`). Since the set stores `String`, you can remove using a borrowed `&str` directly (e.g. based on `text.trim()`) and avoid allocating on every user message.\\n\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/gitbutlerapp/gitbutler/pull/13938#discussion_r3297041332\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-25T08:41:59Z\"}]}}]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"reviews\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"copilot-pull-request-reviewer\"},\"state\":\"COMMENTED\",\"body\":\"## Pull request overview\\n\\nAdds a new public, bounded “projection” API in `but-agentlog` for Agent Trail consumers, exposing PR-relevant agent evidence (sessions/turns/records) via opaque handles and allowlisted/redacted fields, while enriching stored transcripts with prompt/tool provenance metadata.\\n\\n**Changes:**\\n- Extend transcript parsing + GitMeta storage to capture prompt provenance (`prompt_source`), tool classification (`tool_kind`), and tool outcomes (`exit_code`/`outcome`), plus Codex thread source.\\n- Introduce a new public `projection` module that projects PR evidence with strict bounds, redaction, handle hashing, and file-path extraction from patch-like tool inputs.\\n- Tighten metadata capture/CLI ergonomics: record both review-id and PR review targets, and allow reading metadata from bare repos for `show` and explicit `skim`.\\n\\n### Reviewed changes\\n\\nCopilot reviewed 9 out of 9 changed files in this pull request and generated 2 comments.\\n\\n<details>\\n<summary>Show a summary per file</summary>\\n\\n| File | Description |\\r\\n| ---- | ----------- |\\r\\n| crates/but-agentlog/src/transcript.rs | Adds prompt/tool provenance tagging and Codex call-id mapping; expands tests. |\\r\\n| crates/but-agentlog/src/redaction.rs | Adds absolute-path redaction and related path heuristics + tests. |\\r\\n| crates/but-agentlog/src/projection.rs | New public PR projection API with opaque handles, bounds, and allowlisted fields. |\\r\\n| crates/but-agentlog/src/lib.rs | Exposes the new `projection` module publicly. |\\r\\n| crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/write.rs | Persists new transcript fields (prompt source, tool kind, exit code/outcome). |\\r\\n| crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/tests.rs | Adds projection tests and extends record-kind/tool-kind assertions. |\\r\\n| crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/records_outline.rs | Threads `record_hash` through in-memory (skipped in serde) and reads new stored fields. |\\r\\n| crates/but-agentlog/src/environment.rs | Emits both review-id and pull-request review target keys. |\\r\\n| crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs | Supports reading metadata in bare repos for `show` and explicit `skim`. |\\n</details>\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\",\"submittedAt\":\"2026-05-25T08:41:59Z\"}]}}}}}","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-25T08:56:05.993Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}